msgctxt "#32120"
msgid "Windows hardware decode"
msgstr "Windows hardware decode"

msgctxt "#32121"
msgid "On Windows only: D3D11VA (GPU) for 10-bit / HDR / Dolby Vision HEVC (~25–30% faster on 4K HDR/DV). Not for general use — 1080p H.264 SDR should use software decode (often faster, especially on deep seeks); long-interval SDR uses fps-batch per tile. Skipped for AVC and SDR 8-bit HEVC. After the first HW failure on a file, software decode is used for the rest of that job. Requires a full Windows ffmpeg build (e.g. Gyan full from Run). No effect on Linux or CoreELEC."
msgstr "On Windows only: D3D11VA (GPU) for 10-bit / HDR / Dolby Vision HEVC (~25–30% faster on 4K HDR/DV). Not for general use — 1080p H.264 SDR should use software decode (often faster, especially on deep seeks); long-interval SDR uses fps-batch per tile. Skipped for AVC and SDR 8-bit HEVC. After the first HW failure on a file, software decode is used for the rest of that job. Requires a full Windows ffmpeg build (e.g. Gyan full from Run). No effect on Linux or CoreELEC."

